            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/htt-000F/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>htt-000F</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/forest/htt-000F/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="slice of augmented simplicial sets">slice of augmented simplicial sets</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  Given two <fr:link href="/forest/htt-000A/" title="augmented simplicial set" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/htt-000A/" display-uri="htt-000A" type="local">augmented simplicial sets</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X, Y]]></fr:tex>, the Day convolution definition of their <fr:link href="/forest/htt-000B/" title="join of (augmented) simplicial set" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/htt-000B/" display-uri="htt-000B" type="local">joins</fr:link> induces an internal hom functor
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[(Y \mathbin {/} X)_k = \int _{m, n} [n]^{[k] \oplus  [m]} \times  X_m \to  Y_n]]></fr:tex>
  right adjoint to the join functor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(- \star  X)]]></fr:tex>. This is the augmented version of <fr:link href="/forest/htt-000E/" title="slice of simplicial sets" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/htt-000E/" display-uri="htt-000E" type="local">slice simplicial sets</fr:link>. More concretely, we have
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[(Y \mathbin {/} X)_k = \hom _{\mathsf {asSet}}([k] \star  X, Y),]]></fr:tex>
  and the face and degeneracy maps act in the obvious way.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
  The <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(-1)]]></fr:tex>-simplices, or colors, of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y \mathbin {/} X]]></fr:tex> is given by maps <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex>. Since each connected component can only be assigned one color, we can decompose
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[Y \mathbin {/} X = \coprod _{p : X \to  Y} Z_p]]></fr:tex>
  where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Z_p]]></fr:tex> is some simplicial set equipped with the <fr:link href="/forest/htt-000A/" title="augmented simplicial set" uri="https://trebor-huang.github.io/forest/htt-000A/" display-uri="htt-000A" type="local">codiscrete augmentation</fr:link>. Expanding the definitions, we see that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Z_p]]></fr:tex> satisfies the property that maps <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \to  Z_p]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> is a simplicial set, is in bijection with maps <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \star  X \to  Y]]></fr:tex>, such that the composition <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \to  K \star  X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>. If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> have codiscrete augmentation, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Z_p]]></fr:tex> is exactly <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_{/p}]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
  For general augmented simplicial sets, we can also similarly define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_{/p}]]></fr:tex>, which would be an <html:em>unaugmented</html:em> simplicial set. Then we have the isomorphism
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[(Y \mathbin {/} X) = \coprod _{p : X \to  Y} Y_{/p}.]]></fr:tex>
  If we replace <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[k] \oplus  [m]]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[m] \oplus  [k]]]></fr:tex> in the definition, then we get the right adjoint functor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X \star  -) \dashv  (X \mathbin {\backslash } Y)]]></fr:tex>, and correspondingly the coslice construction.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
